1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO PUBLIC SCHOOLS; AMENDING THE TEACHER RESIDENCY
3 ACT; PROVIDING THAT THE AMOUNT OF THE STIPEND FOR A TEACHING
4 RESIDENT BE SET AT A PERCENTAGE OF THE STATUTORY MINIMUM
5 SALARY FOR LEVEL ONE TEACHERS BASED ON THE RESIDENT'S
6 QUALIFICATIONS; PROVIDING THAT A TEACHING RESIDENT MAY WORK
7 AT ANY PUBLIC SCHOOL AFTER THE RESIDENCY INSTEAD OF A PUBLIC
8 SCHOOL IN THE SPONSORING SCHOOL DISTRICT; PROVIDING THAT A
9 PARTNER SCHOOL DISTRICT OR CHARTER SCHOOL SHALL BE EXPECTED
10 TO OFFER EMPLOYMENT TO A TEACHING RESIDENT DEPENDING ON THE
11 DISTRICT'S OR CHARTER SCHOOL'S STAFFING NEEDS AND THE
12 RESIDENT'S PERFORMANCE.
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
15 SECTION 1. Section 22-10B-4 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 2020,
16 Chapter 25, Section 4, as amended) is amended to read:
17 "22-10B-4. TEACHER RESIDENCY PROGRAM COMPONENTS.--A
18 teacher residency program established pursuant to the Teacher
Residency Act shall include:
19
A. competitive admission requirements with
20
multiple criteria;
21
B. rigorous department-approved teacher
22
preparation program coursework, which shall be offered while
23
the teaching resident undertakes a full academic year of
24
guided apprenticeship in the classroom of a level two or
25 HB 30
