1 level three teacher at the partner school district or charter
2 school;
3 C. a co-teaching approach to expose teaching
4 residents to a variety of teaching methods, philosophies and
5 classroom environments;
6 D. clear criteria for the selection of level two
7 and level three teachers based on measures of teacher
8 effectiveness and the appropriate subject area knowledge;
9 E. providing level two and level three teachers
10 with ongoing evidence-based training in coaching and
11 mentoring teaching residents and compensation for time and
12 added responsibility;
13 F. grouping teaching residents in cohorts to
14 facilitate professional collaboration among residents and
15 placing teaching residents in teaching schools or
16 professional development programs that are organized to
support a high-quality teacher learning experience in a
17
supportive work environment;
18
G. measures of appropriate progress through the
19
program;
20
H. for a teaching resident who is an
21
undergraduate, a stipend of no less than sixty-five percent
22
of the statutory minimum salary for a level one teacher and,
23
for a teaching resident who has a bachelor's degree, a
24
stipend of no less than eighty percent of the statutory
