1 minimum salary for a level one teacher;
2 I. a stipend of no less than two thousand dollars
3 ($2,000) per year for level two and level three teachers
4 participating in the program;
5 J. a stipend of no less than two thousand dollars
6 ($2,000) per year for principals or head administrators at
7 the partner school district or charter school;
8 K. funding of no less than fifty thousand dollars
9 ($50,000) per year for teacher residency program coordinators
10 at each department-approved New Mexico teacher residency
11 program;
12 L. a post-completion commitment by teaching
13 residents to serve a minimum of three years at a public
14 school;
15 M. an expectation of an offer of employment to the
16 teaching resident from the partner school district or charter
school, depending on the district's or charter school's
17
staffing needs and the resident's performance;
18
N. support for teaching residents for not less
19
